==English==
===Etymology===
From Old English, ''[[fæthm]]'', meaning outstretched arms. Of [[Germanic]] origins.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-fathom.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
# {{nautical}} A [[unit]] of [[length]] equal to six [[foot|feet]], used mainly for measuring [[depth]]s in [[sea]]s or [[ocean]]s.

